entry.title: leoherzog/TorrentParts
entry.summary:
📑 A website to inspect and edit what's in your Torrent file or Magnet link

Torrent 🧲 Parts

What is this?

BitTorrent is a ubiquitous and powerful way to transfer files peer-to-peer. To specify what file(s) to download with your client, you need to input either a Torrent file or Magnet URL. Torrent Parts is a client-side static web app to read and edit the metadata of a Torrent file or Magnet URL so you know what you're downloading, before you add it to your Torrent client.

Features

  • 📑 Display metadata of a Torrent file, Magnet URL, or URL to a Torrent file (CORS required)
  • 📝 Edit title, comment, Tracker URLs, and Webseeds
  • ↔️ Save and convert between Torrent file and Magnet URL
  • 🔗 Generate a link directly to Torrent Parts with prefilled info[1]
  • 🌐 Add currently known working trackers from newTrackon
  • 👥 Fetch files metadata for a Magnet URL via WebTorrent
  • ℹ️ Learn the basic parts of Torrent metadata and what they mean
  • 🔒 Fully client-side, no files leave your computer

1. Just include the Magnet URL after https://torrent.parts/#, like so.

Special Thanks

This project wouldn't be possible without the fantastic work of:

  • @feross and contributors, for parse-torrent and WebTorrent
  • @cvisuri, for design work
  • @CorralPeltzer, for newTrackon
  • @substack and contributors, for Browserify
  • Cloudflare Pages hosting
